For my primary social media site that i interact with others on I spend time on discord me and a group of friends have a group on discord primarily to schedule and organize dnd games as well as general chatting its nice to have a easy way to reach them and to be part of group chats 
I define digitial literacy as having the skills to parse through the information that can come from digital sources and naviagte through digital spaces effectivly a example from discord is being able to find and join new discord groups and telling what kind and the quality of information they are sharing such as how funny the groups memes are 
one way i have used digital litercy to help maintain online relationships is just the direct way sending messages through discord in order to reach out and organize games or any other events we plan on having
My personal communciton style is to stay quite on social media and not post unless i know the person and need to send a message to them so discord that limits the group to just people i know reflects that well very enough
