Post: ai updated
Hi everyone, I’m Caleb. I’m here to earn my degree in Computer Science! My primary social media site is Discord. A group of my friends and I have a server there where we organize our D&D games and just hang out. It’s a great, easy way to stay connected.
To me, digital literacy means being able to navigate digital spaces and filter through the information you find there. For example, on Discord, it means knowing how to find the right groups and telling what the "vibe" or quality of a server is based on what they post (like their memes!).
Digital literacy helps me maintain my online friendships because it gives me the tools to coordinate our schedules and plan events. My personal communication style is pretty quiet; I don’t usually post unless I’m messaging someone I know. Discord fits me perfectly because it lets me stick to smaller groups of friends.
